Medical doctor and life coach, Dr Sindi Van Zyl has passed away. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Medical doctor and life coach, Dr Sindi Van Zyl has passed away. The much-loved "people's doctor" was 45-years-old. Her employer Kaya FM confirmed the news, saying she passed away in a Johannesburg hospital on SaturdayÂ morning. Van Zyl had been in hospital for weeks battling COVID-19-related complications. She was well known on social media for sharing HIV-related, mental health and other medical information. Just this week, South Africans raised over R1-million for her medical fees. She is survived by her husband and two children.